These sons of bitches
will destroy you

27:01.369 --> 27:03.163
if I tell them to.

27:03.246 --> 27:05.999
- Well, what I'm about to say
may make you sic 'em on me.

27:06.082 --> 27:08.293
- Yeah?
What are you on about?

27:08.376 --> 27:10.378
- A good while ago,

27:10.462 --> 27:12.714
your daddy showed up in Rogers.

27:12.797 --> 27:15.884
It was unexpected,
but I was glad to see him.

27:15.967 --> 27:18.303
He said he wanted
to retire, cash out,

27:18.386 --> 27:19.429
and move to Bolivia.

27:19.512 --> 27:21.431
- And you helped him get away.
- No, I wanted to.

27:21.514 --> 27:23.600
But he wanted to launder money
through my church,

27:23.683 --> 27:24.809
so I had to turn him down.

27:24.893 --> 27:26.227
He didn't like that.

27:26.311 --> 27:28.188
He came to my home with a gun,

27:28.271 --> 27:30.023
threatened to hurt my family.

27:30.106 --> 27:33.860
My father saw him
pointing a gun at me,

27:33.943 --> 27:35.195
and he shot him.

27:35.278 --> 27:37.447
- Shot my daddy.

27:37.530 --> 27:39.240
[chuckles]
You're a liar.

27:39.324 --> 27:41.034
You helped him get away
to Bolivia.

27:41.117 --> 27:42.619
You helped him get away.

27:42.702 --> 27:45.580
- No, Junior,
he's dead and buried.

27:45.663 --> 27:47.582
I wish that weren't true,
but it is.

27:47.665 --> 27:54.714
♪ ♪

27:56.007 --> 27:57.425
This belonged to Glendon.

28:06.142 --> 28:07.310
[gun clicks]

28:07.394 --> 28:09.896
- We used to read about you
in the papers.

28:09.979 --> 28:13.066
He'd talk about
how proud he was.

28:13.149 --> 28:14.901
Used to make me fuckin' nuts.

28:14.984 --> 28:18.113
- He was always good to me.

28:18.196 --> 28:20.073
But what I told you
is the truth.

28:20.156 --> 28:22.784
He wasn't the same man
I used to know.

28:22.867 --> 28:24.744
There was a meanness to him.

28:24.828 --> 28:26.287
He had the devil in him,
Junior.

28:26.371 --> 28:29.249
- Holy Roller Eli.

28:29.332 --> 28:31.084
You better than all of us,
ain't you?

28:31.167 --> 28:33.128
- No, sir.

28:33.211 --> 28:36.840
I have the devil in me too.

28:36.923 --> 28:38.675
I think we all do,
but that doesn't mean

28:38.758 --> 28:39.843
he has to win.

28:39.926 --> 28:42.846
[tense music]

28:42.929 --> 28:44.347
♪ ♪

28:44.431 --> 28:45.807
- Hey, boys,
give us a minute.

28:45.890 --> 28:47.183
Go on, go on, go on.

28:47.267 --> 28:54.065
♪ ♪

28:54.858 --> 28:56.860
He was a asshole anyway.

28:56.943 --> 28:59.112
- I'm sorry, Junior.

28:59.821 --> 29:01.030
- Yeah.

29:04.701 --> 29:07.287
You know, that reporter
did come to see me, Eli.

29:07.370 --> 29:08.580
Came snooping.

29:08.663 --> 29:10.623
That's what got me
thinking on you.

29:10.707 --> 29:12.459
I didn't tell him nothing.

29:12.542 --> 29:14.127
- I appreciate it.

29:14.210 --> 29:15.378
You've been
a better friend to me

29:15.462 --> 29:17.130
than I was to you.

29:17.213 --> 29:19.674
- Eli...

29:19.757 --> 29:23.011
Pop was loaded with some cash
last time I saw him.

29:23.094 --> 29:25.513
- I believe I can probably
help you find it.

29:25.597 --> 29:28.016
- I'd feel good about that.

29:28.099 --> 29:30.685
- So no more threats,

29:30.768 --> 29:32.896
no more sending motorcycle men
to kill me.

29:32.979 --> 29:35.106
- I had nothing to do
with you getting shot, Eli.

29:35.190 --> 29:37.942
- Junior, it's okay.
I forgive you.

29:38.026 --> 29:39.986
- I'm telling you the truth,
Eli.

29:40.069 --> 29:42.322
I did not send
no motorcycle men.

29:42.405 --> 29:45.325
[dramatic music]

29:45.408 --> 29:47.494
♪ ♪

29:53.124 --> 29:55.210
[explosion]

29:55.293 --> 29:58.296
[alarms blaring]

29:58.379 --> 30:00.632
- Hey, let me out of here!

30:00.715 --> 30:02.091
[pounding]

30:02.175 --> 30:04.052
♪ ♪

30:04.135 --> 30:06.554
[yelling]

30:06.638 --> 30:09.390
- Weaver, you all right?

30:09.474 --> 30:10.683
- I can't hear nothing!

30:10.767 --> 30:15.396
♪ ♪

30:15.480 --> 30:17.482
- You gotta be shitting me!

30:17.565 --> 30:19.359
♪ ♪

30:19.442 --> 30:22.362
[engines roaring]

30:22.445 --> 30:29.202
♪ ♪

30:36.125 --> 30:38.044
choir: ♪ O Father ♪

30:38.127 --> 30:39.420
♪ O Satan ♪

30:39.504 --> 30:41.297
♪ O Sun ♪

30:41.381 --> 30:44.259
♪ Let the children
come to thee ♪

30:44.342 --> 30:47.303
♪ Behold the morning star ♪

30:47.387 --> 30:49.472
♪ Akephalos ♪

30:49.556 --> 30:52.141
♪ Shine through me ♪

30:52.225 --> 30:55.478
♪ Come forth in war ♪

30:55.562 --> 30:58.064
♪ Come forth in peace ♪

30:58.147 --> 31:03.903
♪ Like a day
without the dawn ♪

31:03.987 --> 31:09.450
♪ Like a ray void of the sun ♪

31:09.534 --> 31:14.914
♪ Like a storm
that brings no calm ♪

31:14.998 --> 31:21.129
♪ I'm most complete
yet so undone ♪

31:21.212 --> 31:24.132
[vocalizing]

31:24.215 --> 31:31.180
♪ ♪

31:45.903 --> 31:48.823
- [low indistinct speech]

31:48.906 --> 31:55.872
♪ ♪

32:03.421 --> 32:05.340
[bright tone]
